{"word":"ἠρέμα","slug":"ἠρέμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἠρέμα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>like <a href='S:ἀτρέμας'><el>ἀτρέμας</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>stilly, quietly, gently, softly</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a little, slightly</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>slowly</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>τάχιστα</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>deriv.</a> uncertain\n"}]}